message.content:
I need to remove CSS that was added to C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\Canvas\CanvasEditor.module.css. 

The following block needs to be removed (everything from `.descriptionInput` through the dark theme variant, right before `.shareButton`):

```
.descriptionInput {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
    border: 1px solid rgba(18, 24, 31, 0.12);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
    padding: 0.35rem 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.74rem;
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    color: var(--atelier-ink);
    outline: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
}

.descriptionInput::placeholder {
    color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--atelier-ink) 40%, transparent);
}

.descriptionInput:focus {
    border-color: var(--atelier-accent);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
}

[data-theme="dark"] .descriptionInput {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
    color: #e0ddd8;
}

[data-theme="dark"] .descriptionInput:focus {
    border-color: var(--atelier-accent);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
}
```

Use sed to remove lines containing descriptionInput and the surrounding rules. The file path is /c/Users/johnm/iskrib_v3/client/src/components/HomePage/Canvas/CanvasEditor.module.css

Actually, it's probably easier to use a Python or node script to do the removal. Find the line with `.descriptionInput {` and remove everything up to and including the blank line before `.shareButton {`.

